Date: Tue, 26 May 2026 10:01:50 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] patch 0879: Forward outlook - classify capex + explain
 "mixed"
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

NGL Fine Chem audit: the single line "Forward outlook: mixed -
capacity / capex expansion + forward guidance" was not informative
enough. User wants to know two things at-a-glance:
  (1) is this MAINTENANCE capex or GROWTH capex - and what specifically
      do they do with it?
  (2) when verdict is "mixed", what comments produced that mix?

Now renders as 3 lines:
  Line 1 - base direction (unchanged): "Forward outlook: mixed - capacity /
           capex expansion + forward guidance"
  Line 2 - capex classification: "Capex: GROWTH - Phase II commercial
           production from H2FY27 - ₹210 Cr greenfield Tarapur - new products"
           (color-coded: green=growth / amber=maintenance / orange=mixed)
  Line 3 - mixed reason: "Why mixed: ⬆ <positive snippets> · ⚠ <cautious
           snippets>" pulling actual tone-signal sentences

Implementation:
  - snapshot.ts: extended forwardLook with optional capex {type, purpose,
    evidenceQuote} and mixedReason {positives[], cautions[]}.
  - india-build.ts: classify capex via growthKW (greenfield/brownfield/
    new product/capacity expansion/Phase N/etc) vs maintKW (replacement/
    refurbish/retrofit). Extract purpose phrases (Phase milestone, ₹ Cr
    amount, greenfield/brownfield modifier, new-products mention).
    Pull positive + cautious tone snippets when grade is mixed/cautious/weak.
  - IndiaInstitutionalReport.tsx: render the new fields when present;
    falls back to single-line behavior when no concall data available.
